Customer Churn Prediction in E-Commerce
📌 Project Overview

This project aims to develop a machine learning model to predict customer churn in an e-commerce company.

Customer churn significantly impacts revenue, and early detection allows businesses to implement targeted retention strategies instead of mass promotions.

🎯 Business Problem

The company currently lacks a predictive system to identify customers at risk of churn.

As a result:

Retention campaigns are applied broadly

Promotion costs are inefficient

Revenue loss occurs due to undetected churn

🧠 Objective

To build a classification model that:

Predicts customer churn

Achieves high recall for churn detection

Supports targeted retention strategy

Reduces potential revenue loss

📊 Dataset Information

Total records: 3,941 customers

Target variable: Churn (0 = No, 1 = Yes)

Churn rate: 17%

Key features include:

Satisfaction Score

Complaint

Day Since Last Order

Cashback Amount

Tenure

Each row represents one unique customer.

⚙️ Methodology
1️⃣ Data Preparation

Missing value imputation (median)

One-hot encoding for categorical variables

Stratified train-test split

Class imbalance handling using class_weight='balanced'

2️⃣ Modeling

Models evaluated:

Logistic Regression

Random Forest

Evaluation metric:

Recall (primary)

ROC AUC (secondary)

Final model selected:

Logistic Regression (Recall = 79%, ROC AUC = 0.87)

📈 Model Performance

Recall (Churn): 79%

Accuracy: 80%

ROC AUC: 0.87

The model successfully detects 8 out of 10 churn customers.

💰 Business Impact Simulation

Assumption:

Revenue loss per churn: Rp 300,000

If 100 customers churn:

79 can be detected

Potential revenue protected: Rp 23.7 million

This enables efficient and targeted retention strategy.

🎯 Risk Segmentation Strategy

Customers are segmented into:

High Risk → Personalized retention offer

Medium Risk → Reminder & soft promotion

Low Risk → No intervention

🚀 Implementation Plan

Monthly churn scoring

Quarterly model retraining

Integration with CRM system

⚠️ Limitations

Based on historical data

No Customer Lifetime Value (CLV) included

Not real-time streaming data

External market factors not considered

